715325f-b.text:
Vest 124th Street, west from St. Nicholas Avenue. Across the view, behind the gasoline station, are buildings on the west side of Morningside Avenue. Those to the left, at the S. W. corner are owned John D. Rockefeller and will be demolished according to the New York Times article of Oct. 5, 1938. Hancock Place runs in the line of the streetcar tracks in the foreground. The vague structure in the background is the International House.
1: September, 1928
2: September, 1927
George L. Balgue, photo

715326f-a.text:
W. 124th Street, east from St. Iicholas Avenue. Note the Ninth Avenue Elevated Line running in a north and southward direction on Eighth Avenue. The white building seen at the left is now (1938) gone; having been replaced by a business structure. It bears No. 280 St. Nicholas Avenue and is at the N.E. corner.
July 1929.
Geo. L. Balgue
